Package com.phasmidsoftware.dsaipg.util.benchmark

package com.phasmidsoftware.dsaipg.util.benchmark
  • Class
    Description
    Benchmark<T>
    Interface to define the behavior of a Benchmark.
    Benchmark_Timer<T>
    This class implements a simple Benchmark utility for measuring the running time of algorithms.
    OperationsBenchmark
    The OperationsBenchmark class is responsible for benchmarking operations on arrays of integers such as finding the largest integer, comparing adjacent elements, and their optimized variant.
    PQBenchmark
    The PQBenchmark class is designed to benchmark operations performed with priority queues.
    SortBenchmark
    This class runs a suite of sorting benchmarks.
    SortBenchmarkHelper
    A utility class designed to provide helper methods for benchmarking and testing sorting algorithms.
    SorterBenchmark<T extends Comparable<T>>
    Class to extend Benchmark_Timer for sorting an array of T values.
    Statistics
    The Statistics class is designed to analyze and store statistical data for a series of numerical values.
    StatPack
    The StatPack class serves as a container for managing and tracking statistical data across multiple keys.
    Stopwatch
    Simple benchmarking tool: Stopwatch.
    SymbolTableBenchmark
    Class to test the comparative efficiency of: (1) build a hash table and get the values in key order; (2) build a Red-black tree and the values in key order.
    TimeLogger
    Class to handle logging of times, both raw and normalized.
    Timer
    Class which is able to time the running of functions.
